    <p>Alisha Ramos is a Director of Product Design at Vox Media and lives in Washington, D.C. At Vox Media, she oversees product design for the revenue group, with a special focus on products and platforms that help tell brand partners' stories both on- and off-platform. She played an integral part in building the branded content and partnerships business at Vox (now Vox Creative) and has been considered <a href="http://www.niemanlab.org/author/aramos/">a thought leader</a> in the cross-section between editorial, product, and design. She was named <a href="http://tech.co/dcfemtech-recognizes-top-30-women-programmers-2015-04">"one of DC's Most Powerful Women Programmers" in 2015 by DCFemTech</a>.</p>

    <p>In a former life, she worked in brand strategy consulting for Fortune 500 companies at Prophet, a global consulting firm.</p>

    <p>Alisha earned her Bachelor's degree from Harvard University, where she focused on Sociology and History. While at Harvard, she ran a digital publication called <i>The Harvard Voice</i>.</p>

